 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to record mathematical values. A
mathematical value can be used in the definition of a mathematical function or
maths space, or in the identification of a property value.</p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
<li>a maths value that is a real value;</li>
<li>a maths value that is an integer value;</li>
<li>a maths value that is a complex value;</li>
<li>a maths value that is a Boolean value;</li>
<li>a maths value that is a tuple of other maths values.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
<li><p>array and matrix values;</p></li>
<li><p>the association of units with a mathematical value.</p>
<note>The use of a mathematical value to identify a property
value with respect to a scale is within the scope of the
<module_ref linkend="property_identification:1_scope">Property_identification</module_ref> application module.</note>
</li>
 </outscope>

